OL,3,CGuernsey's Deputy Chief Minister
OL,4,Cavoids suspension
OL,6,FHowever, he argued he only confirmed a
OL,7,Fseries of facts to the journalist,
OL,8,Fdescribing the calls to suspend him as
OL,9,F"extraordinary and dystopian".
OL,11,FPoliticians largely backed Deputy St
OL,12,FPier following a debate which saw 22
OL,13,Fpoliticians vote against his
OL,14,Fsuspension and 11 support it.
OL,16,FDeputy St Pier defended himself,
OL,17,Fstating he was advocating for several
OL,18,Ffamilies with safeguarding concerns
OL,19,Fabout Guernsey's medical sector.
